    <note>Chen(1) Zan(3) [15201] In 1275, as a private subject (buyi), he memorialized about defense policies, but was not heard. In 1276-7, he brought his family financial resources to the coast and gave them to Zhang(1) Shijie [15200] in order to support the navy. He attacked and killed Lin(1) Hua (not in dataset), thereby regaining Xinghua. Zhao(1) Duanzong [9017] appointed his in charge of military affairs and he regained Fuzhou and Quanzhou. Then he fought valiantly, was captured, refused to submit and was put to death. CBD, 3, 2534.</note>
